Midgaard's High Court has issued a formal interdiction judgment following the institutional assessment: the Grand Vent-Oracle of the Ash Cult must be silenced. The Court's determination is that the Oracle's genuine geological intuition — corrupted by decades of theological interpretation — has been the source of the Cult's institutional authority; every doctrine-speaker and archivist derives legitimacy from her pronouncements. Without the Oracle's voice, the Ash Cult's claim to interpret the Speaking Vent collapses. The interdiction is binding under civic law.
The Grand Vent-Oracle has been silenced and Midgaard's High Court has formally dissolved the Ash Cult's institutional status under the interdiction judgment. Observers at the Speaking Vent report that the vent has continued its eruption cycle without any new interpretations being filed, and the remaining doctrine-speakers are disputing each other's authority in the Oracle's absence. The High Archive notes with some irony that the mountain is still speaking; it is only the translators who have gone quiet.
